        "Negotiate TLS security",
        "Send the HTTP request",
        "Receive and download the response",
        "Parse the downloaded resources",
        "Render the page"
      ],
      "feedback": "The browser first finds the server’s address, then establishes TCP and secures it with TLS. It can then exchange HTTP data, download the response, parse its resources, and render the resulting page."
    },
    {
      "format": "multipleChoice",
      "context": "A page’s HTML arrives successfully. While parsing it, the browser encounters a stylesheet link and several script elements, then eventually displays the page.",
      "question": "Why does parsing matter before rendering?",
      "options": [
        {
          "feedback": "Parsing turns the downloaded HTML and related resources into structures the browser can use, such as a document tree and style information. Rendering uses those structures to decide what appears on screen.",
          "isCorrect": true,
          "text": "It converts downloaded data into structures that can be rendered."
        },
        {
          "feedback": "The network connection has already delivered the bytes, so parsing is not what transports them. Parsing interprets the contents after download.",
          "isCorrect": false,
          "text": "It creates the network connection to the server."
        },
        {
          "feedback": "HTTP status codes come from the server’s response, before the browser renders the page. Parsing is instead about understanding the page’s content and structure.",
          "isCorrect": false,
          "text": "It decides which HTTP status code the server should return."
        },
        {
          "feedback": "Parsing does not replace downloading; it operates on downloaded bytes. The browser needs the parsed structure to lay out and paint the page correctly.",
          "isCorrect": false,
          "text": "It downloads every resource without interpreting it."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "format": "selectImage",
      "question": "A waterfall shows the HTML response fully downloaded, but the page is not painted until a stylesheet finishes loading. Which image best represents this situation?",
      "options": [
